track_notes:
I used the SDW LDP on my up route but took the shorter bridleway coming down. As I was travelling from the south I parked on the west side of the A24 near Parkfield Farm and crossed the road on foot. Nice far reaching views from the summit -
30 mins up and 25 mins down.

Total time (including ops): 1h 30m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Chanctonbury Ring Linear from West. Apr 2025.
